Results will help to better understand the impact of frailty and functional 
ability on outcomes in elderly STEMI patients undergoing primary angioplasty, 
thus potentially contributing to improving their clinical management. Higher 
life expectancy has resulted in a large segment of elderly population and an 
increase in myocardial infarction in these patients. This calls attention to 
healthcare systems to focus on promoting methods to improve the clinical 
management of this population.

